Disable the native OpenMW Hide UI input action (A_ToggleHUD).

We want the Hide UI key/button (default F11, or any controller binding) to do
nothing when triggered, because the companion drives HUD visibility itself
(Vanilla/DS mode). Every binding dispatches through
ActionManager::executeAction(A_ToggleHUD), so dropping the body of that one
case — leaving just the break — disables the action for all bindings without
touching anything else. The Lua I.UI.setHudVisibility binding and the mwscript
ToggleHUD command are separate code paths and remain fully functional, so the
companion can still control HUD visibility programmatically.

diff --git a/apps/openmw/mwinput/actionmanager.cpp b/apps/openmw/mwinput/actionmanager.cpp
--- a/apps/openmw/mwinput/actionmanager.cpp
+++ b/apps/openmw/mwinput/actionmanager.cpp
@@ -116,6 +116,7 @@
                 quickKey(10);
                 break;
             case A_ToggleHUD:
-                windowManager->setHudVisibility(!windowManager->isHudVisible());
+                // COMPANION: native Hide UI action disabled - HUD visibility is driven by
+                // the companion (Vanilla/DS mode), not this key/button toggle.
                 break;
             case A_ToggleDebug:
